task.summary: Default task
Finished adding Model Fields. Generated a form from the model, attached it to a template that will display the form and commit inputs to the database.
Added a history page of all jobs that are in the database. Included functionality to sort the list by the different fields.
Adjusted Histroy page to show less information, and links on the history page that take you to a details page for each list item.
Adjusted Histroy page to show less information, and links on the history page that take you to a details page for each list item.
Started on putting together the edit page and the forms needed to adjust db records.
Added an edit function, and entries in the database can now be edited and saved.
Edit and delete views are finished.
Partial commit
Added an API to the home page that pulls a random quote from zenQuotes API and presents it on the screen.
Added an API to the home page that pulls a random quote from zenQuotes API and presents it on the screen. The json request is also printed to the terminal.
Changed to a different API with more functionality. Incorporated a new template page rather than the homepage.
Finally finished integrating the data from the API response into the template. Currently everything works. QOL improvements tomorrow.
Last touches on the API search element.
Added a request to a website to scrape some data for the homepage using beautifulsoup
Updated HTML and CSS to normalize styling across all pages.

Added minimum and maximum salary columns to the job search. The search view will populate those values from the API result if the values are available. Commmiting before adjusting the Model for addition of these data to the db

Adjusted the main database so that it would more easily fit the data that the search function was looking for. Added a temporary database so that I can save the data searched for and then populate the database with those data if the user chooses to.

Setup the test page so that it has the same functionality as the API search. Adjusted it so that it returns the data from the API search and inputs them into forms on the page. (in order to allow them to be saved to the main database.

Got the data from the search to be save-able, although it looks strange right now. All the code is still in the test template and needs to be transferred over. But I wanted to save it while It was working.

Again all the saves are working, the styling is updated. There are still several pieces of functionality that I want to work on. But after that this will be done. Going to try and move the test data into the main search view.
Restore point before deleting test.
Test removed, final commit for branch
Adjusted some comments and minor code
Changed the field in JobScraping_input so that it only accepted the formatted date required.
Refactored saveSearch so that it is 20 lines shorter. Changed searchResults so that they display the whole day of the month and not just the first digit.
Re-added the High temperature section of the home page and it worked this time.
Set up the search results so that you can click a link to the original job posting on the results page. Also made is so that saved job posts had a link to the original job posting as well.
Fixed the footer on the Job search page by adding it directly to the table.
Added JobScraping_footer.html
Added error page for when the API doesn't send a response.
